cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and classification of tweets. It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves identifying clickbait content in tweets. Additionally, the use of neural networks for classification makes cs.LG (Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories. Finally, the use of bi-directional Gated Recurrent Units (biGRU) suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
